            "id": "4530672",
            "title": "Lululemon delivers solid Q3 report, begins hunt for new CEO; shares soar",
            "description": "<html><body><p data-eci=\"true\" data-pm-slice=\"0 0 []\">Shares of Lululemon Athletica (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/LULU\" title=\"lululemon athletica inc.\">LULU</a></span>) are soaring in the afterhours of trading on Thursday after the athleisure wear company raised its full-year forecast, posted a solid third-quarter report, and boosted its stock buyback program by $1B.</p>\n<p>LULU is<span style=\"color: #008000;\"> up 10.2%</span> postmarket in the U.S. Stock is down more than 50% so far this year.</p>\n<p>The company, separately, announced that it has hired an executive search firm to help find its next candidate for the top job, as current chief executive Calvin McDonald will step down at the end of January next year. It also said board chair Marti Morfitt will take on the expanded role of executive chair, effective immediately.</p>\n<p>For fiscal 2025, Lululemon now expects earnings per share between $12.92 and $13.02 (mid $12.97; est. $12.89), raised from the prior guide of $12.77 to $12.97 per share. It expects net revenue between $10.96B and $11.05B (mid $11.01B; est. $10.96B), from a previous range of $10.85B to $11B.</p>\n<p>During Q3, the Americas segment saw a 2% decline in revenue, which was offset by a 33% revenue surge in the International segment.</p>\n<p>Total comparable sales for Lululemon on a constant currency basis were up 2%, much ahead of the 0.72% estimate polled by Bloomberg.</p>\n<p>The company opened 12 new stores during Q3, bringing its total to 796 stores, while inventories rose 11% to $2B at the end of the quarter.</p>\n<p>Net income for the three months ended November 2 was $306.8M, compared with $351.9M last year. The metric was hurt by a nearly $80M increase in SG&amp;A expenses.</p>\n<p>On a per-share basis, the company earned $2.59 apiece, much ahead of the average analyst estimate of $2.22 earnings per share.</p>\n<p>Revenue rose 7% to $2.57B and topped the estimate of $2.48B.</p>\n<p>\"We delivered better-than-expected revenue and EPS in the third quarter as a result of our disciplined execution and ongoing strength internationally,\" CFO Meghan Frank said.</p>\n<p>Additionally, the company said its board approved a $1B increase to its share repurchase program, bringing its total buyback capacity to $1.6B.</p>\n<div class=\"signup_widget_placeholder\"></div>\n</body></html>",
            "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/assets/og_image_1200-29b2bfe1a595477db6826bd2126c63ac2091efb7ec76347a8e7f81ba17e3de6c.png",
